. Visual aids such as the U-Pb concordia diagram, the Rb-Sr isochron, or the fission track radial plot can be very useful for the exploratory analysis of geochronological data. The ternary diagram and logratio plot play the same role for helium thermochronology, as they bring out the full information content of U-Th-(Sm)-He data, and can help to reveal patterns between aliquots and samples that may not be seen otherwise.
